task.summary: Ported algorithm from Python and started work on graphical representation.
Got animation working, but having trouble with it sometimes not solving

Added a shuffle method to Board class
- This ensures that randomly generated boards are solvable. - Also started setup for a 15-puzzle.

Cleaned up code for submission
- Also added README description of algorithm

Fixed Tile class and added testing
- Added function for checking if tile is blank and updated code accordingly. - Added a constant for a blank tile. - Added tests for Tile class.

Board class refactor
- Refactored the board class, making improvements as necessary. - Added the linear conflict algorithm to the board cost function. - Added tests for board class. - Minor changes to Tile class and tests.

BoardNode class refactor
- Refactored the board node class, making improvements as necessary. - Added tests for board node class.

Completed core JS work and fixed issues
- Refactored the AStarSolver class and the main TileBoard React component. - Resolved issues with the board never getting solved (likely due to bad async coding in TileBoard component). - Added tests for AStarSolver class. - Added new methods (and tests for them) to some of the lower level core classes. - Started work on a new Tile React components, but haven't made much progress yet.

Started work on Rust implementation
- Completed the Tile struct, methods, and unit tests. - Started work on board struct, methods, and unit tests. - Small change to JS code.

Continued work on Rust Board implementation
- Implemented the `Clone`, `PartialEq`, `Eq` and `ToString` traits on the Board struct. - Added the `_in_conflict`, `index`, `is_valid_move`, and `get_moves` methods. - Added tests for each new method. - Other small code changes.

Continued adding more methods to Board
- Completed `shuffle` function (and test). - Had to add new crate, `rand` - Altered `get_moves` function to be more explicit about lifetimes. - Added methods for `translate_index`, `move_blank_tile` (added content), `_manhattan_cost`, `get_cost` (not complete), and `is_solved`. - Added hash trait implementation to be based only on board tiles. - Added tests for new functions (except `get_cost`).
Nearly complete, committing for testing purposes

More work/optimizations done
- Seems to be in a working state, although not much faster than JS version now.

Made conversion to Web Assembly
- Finished working on Rust implementation. - Improved effectiveness of algorithm by making a second comparison with the manhattan distance plus the number of linear conflicts if the costs are the same (which happens a lot). - Made major changes to project structure to add support for Web Assembly. - Wasm is now fully functional. - Project will now only use Rust code; need to setup an option for using Rust or Javascript.

Started moving tile rendering to another component
- Started by creating a new component, but should probably just add to the tile class that already exists.
